CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1958, pg. A12 reads: "From Quakertowne [sic] came these lovelies: Ruth Ramsey, Virgil Spaulding and Pittsburgh's Wilnetta Jones, front row. In the rear: Irene Conners, Lela Jones, Henrietta Smith and Barbara Abele."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seven Gay Northeasterner members, from left, front row: Ruth Ramsey, Virgil Spaulding, and Wilnetta Jones; back row: Irene Conners, Lela Jones, Henrietta Smith, and Barbara Abele, posed in hallway of Penn Sheraton Hotel for grand ball
